      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:54:5",
      "text": [
        " لَا بَأْسَ أَنْ يَتَخَلَّقَ الرَّجُلُ لِامْرَأَتِهِ وَ لَكِنْ لَا يَبِيتُ مُتَخَلِّقاً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Humey Bin Ziyad, from Al Hassan Bin Muhammad Bin Sama’at, from Ja’far Bin Sama’at, from Aban, from a man who had affirmed it, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> havign said: ‘There is no problem if the man were to apply <span class=\"iTxt\">Al-Khalouq</span> for his wife, but he should not sleep overnight having applied <span class=\"iTxt\">Al-Khalouq</span>’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "5. Humayd ibn Ziyad has narrated from al-Hassan ibn Muhammad ibn Sama‘ah from Ja‘far ibn Sama‘ah from Aban from a man whose name is he has confirmed who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘It is not harmful for one to use al-Khuluq for his wife, but he must not sleep overnight with it.’” "
        ]
      }
